<subsection xml:id="subsec-square-roots-of-numbers-from-a-calculator">
    <title>Square roots of numbers from a calculator</title>
   
    <p>
        The square root button on a calculator is labelled <kbd>√</kbd>. Therefore, to find the square root of a number using a calculator, you press <kbd>√</kbd> followed by the number.
    </p>
    <p>
        Example: To find <m>\sqrt{64}</m> using a calculator, press the button <kbd>√</kbd> followed by the key <kbd>6</kbd> then <kbd>4</kbd> .
    </p>
    <p>
        Next, press the <kbd>=</kbd> sign, then read the displayed results.  
    </p>
    <activity>
        <statement>
            <p>
                
            </p>
            <p>
              1. Working in groups, use a calculator to explore the following:
            </p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Press the <kbd>√</kbd> button on your calculator. What happens when you press it without entering a number?
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Now, press <kbd>√</kbd> then press the key <kbd>2</kbd>,<kbd>5</kbd> then press <kbd>=</kbd> and read the displayed result. 
                    </p>
                </li>
               </ul> 
            </p>
            <p>
               2. Work out the square roots of the following numbers using a calculator:
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)" cols="3">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>0.2025</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>0.1225</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>0.0625</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>0.3025</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>\frac{1}{256}</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>\frac{25}{4096}</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>\frac{49}{100}</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <m>625</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
               3. What happens if you try to find the square root of a negative number, like <m>-16</m>? Does your calculator give an answer?
            </p>
            <p>
                4. Share your work with fellow learners.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </activity>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
              Work out the square roots of the following numbers using a calculator:  
            </p>
            <p>
                Express the answers to 4 significant figures.
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>7223</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>7.744</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           On your calculator, 
                        </p>
                            <p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Press the <kbd>√</kbd> button, then press the key <kbd>7</kbd>,<kbd>2</kbd>,<kbd>2</kbd>,<kbd>3</kbd>, then press the <kbd>=</kbd> sign.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Read the square root of <m>7223</m> on the screen of your calculator.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Therefore, the square root of <m>7223</m> expressed to four significant figure is <m>84.99</m>.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            On your calculator,
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Press the <kbd>√</kbd> button, then press the key <kbd>7</kbd>,<kbd>.</kbd>,<kbd>7</kbd>,<kbd>4</kbd>,<kbd>4</kbd>, then press the <kbd>=</kbd> sign.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Read the square root of <m>7.744</m> on the screen of your calculator.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Therefore, the square root of <m>7.744</m> expressed to four significant figures is <m>2.783</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>

        </solution>
    </example>
</subsection>